microstructure: three main solid-solution phases, including two bcc phases and an amorphous phase
evidence: a 10-element equimolar alloy, CuCoNiCrAlFeMoTiVZr, also exhibited a simple ascast microstructure in which three main solid-solution phases were found, including two bcc phases (lattice constants 2.99 and 3.15 ) and an amorphous phase.
In Figure  5A  the average grain size of the as-splat-quenched CuCoNiCrAlFe-TiV foil is 0.8 lm, whereas that of the as-sputtered Cu 0.5 Co-NiCrAl film shown in Figure  5B  is only 7 nm.

evidence: TEM bright-field images and corresponding SAD patterns of high-entropy alloys: A) as-splat-quenched CuCoNiCrAlFeTiV foil with zone axes [014] and [1 Å 11]; B) as-sputtered Cu 0.5 CoNiCrAl film.
